# LangGraph Support Ticket Triage Agent - Environment Variables Template
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual API keys

# =============================================================================
# LLM API Configuration
# =============================================================================

# Anthropic Claude API Key (Primary LLM Provider)
# Get your API key from: https://console.anthropic.com/
# The agent uses Claude 3 Sonnet for ticket classification, priority detection, 
# summarization, and acknowledgment generation
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_api_key_here

# Alternative LLM Providers (Optional)
# Uncomment and configure if you want to use a different LLM provider
# Note: You'll need to modify the agent code to use these providers

# OpenAI API Key
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# Azure OpenAI Configuration
# AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your_azure_openai_api_key_here
# AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource.openai.azure.com/
# OPENAI_API_VERSION=2024-02-15-preview
# AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT_NAME=your_deployment_name

# Google Gemini API Key
# Get your API key from: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_api_key_here

# AWS Bedrock Configuration (uses AWS credentials)
# Configure AWS credentials using AWS CLI or environment variables
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your_aws_access_key_id
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your_aws_secret_access_key
# AWS_DEFAULT_REGION=us-east-1

# =============================================================================
# Optional Configuration
# =============================================================================

# LangSmith Tracing (Optional - for debugging and monitoring)
# Get your API key from: https://smith.langchain.com/
# LANGCHAIN_TRACING_V2=true
# LANGCHAIN_API_KEY=your_langsmith_api_key_here
# LANGCHAIN_PROJECT=support-triage-agent

# Logging Level (Optional)
# Options: DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR, CRITICAL
# LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# =============================================================================
# Setup Instructions
# =============================================================================

# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp .env.example .env

# 2. Get your Anthropic API key:
#    - Visit https://console.anthropic.com/
#    - Sign up or log in to your account
#    - Navigate to API Keys section
#    - Create a new API key
#    - Copy the key and replace 'your_anthropic_api_key_here' above

# 3. (Optional) Set up LangSmith for debugging:
#    - Visit https://smith.langchain.com/
#    - Create an account and get your API key
#    - Uncomment the LangSmith variables above and add your key

# 4. Save the .env file and run the agent:
#    python support_triage_agent.py

# =============================================================================
# Security Notes
# =============================================================================

# IMPORTANT: Never commit your .env file to version control!
# The .env file is already included in .gitignore to prevent accidental commits.
# 
# Keep your API keys secure:
# - Don't share them in chat, email, or public repositories
# - Rotate keys regularly
# - Use environment-specific keys for development/staging/production
# - Monitor your API usage and billing

# =============================================================================
# Troubleshooting
# =============================================================================

# Common Issues:
# 
# 1. "Anthropic API key is required" error:
#    - Make sure you've copied this file to .env
#    - Verify your API key is correct and active
#    - Check that there are no extra spaces around the key
#
# 2. API rate limiting errors:
#    - Check your Anthropic account usage limits
#    - Consider upgrading your plan if needed
#    - Implement retry logic for production use
#
# 3. Import errors:
#    - Make sure you've installed all dependencies: pip install -r requirements.txt
#    - Verify you're using the correct Python environment
#
# 4. Permission errors:
#    - Ensure the .env file has proper read permissions
#    - Check that your API key has the necessary permissions
